## Kit Setup (for agents)

To set up agentic-kit in a project, run from the **project root** (the directory that contains `agentic-kit/`):

```bash
agentic-kit/tools/init.sh --non-interactive --ide=claude    # Claude Code
agentic-kit/tools/init.sh --non-interactive --ide=cursor   # Cursor
agentic-kit/tools/init.sh --non-interactive --ide=github  # Copilot
agentic-kit/tools/init.sh --non-interactive --ide=all      # all three (alias: --ide=both)
```

Non-interactive flags: `-n`, `--non-interactive`, `--yes`, or `-y`. The script prints a **`[AGENT ACTION REQUIRED]`** block instead of spawning a nested CLI to edit `.agentic-kit-artefacts/PROJECT.md`.

**After the script exits, fill in `.agentic-kit-artefacts/PROJECT.md` yourself:** inspect the project files (`package.json`, `pyproject.toml`, `Cargo.toml`, `go.mod`, `Makefile`, version files, etc.) and replace every `<placeholder>` with the correct value. Then run `agentic-kit/tools/validate-config.sh` to confirm all placeholders are resolved.

**Layout — minimally invasive (the goal):**

```
project root/
├── .agentic-kit-artefacts/        ← single home for kit-managed docs + state
│   ├── PIPELINE.md                ← canonical pipeline (kit-managed; refreshed on init)
│   ├── PROJECT.md                 ← project-specific config (you edit this)
│   ├── memory/                    ← layered memory (auto-managed)
│   ├── features/                  ← active feature folders (created per /vadavik)
│   └── archive/                   ← completed features (moved by Zlydni)
├── CLAUDE.md / AGENTS.md / .github/copilot-instructions.md
│                                  ← thin stub OR your existing file with a managed
│                                    include block <!-- agentic-kit:start --> … --end -->
├── .claude/  .cursor/  .github/   ← agent + skill copies (one folder per IDE)
└── .gitignore                     ← managed block ignores .agentic-kit-artefacts/{memory,features,archive,…}
```

Everything kit-touched is either inside `.agentic-kit-artefacts/`, the IDE folder (`.claude/`, `.cursor/`, `.github/`), or wrapped in a removable `<!-- agentic-kit:start --> … <!-- agentic-kit:end -->` block. `agentic-kit/tools/teardown.sh` either strips the block or removes the file when its SHA-256 still matches the kit copy.

**What each `--ide` produces:**

| Target | Skills | Agents | Pipeline entry-point |
|--------|--------|--------|----------------------|
| `claude` | Copies → `.claude/skills/` | Copies → `.claude/agents/` | `CLAUDE.md` (managed include block → `@.agentic-kit-artefacts/PIPELINE.md`) |
| `cursor` | Copies → `.cursor/skills/` (and `.claude/skills/` for bundled scripts) | Generated `.cursor/agents/*.md` ([subagents](https://cursor.com/docs/context/subagents)) | `AGENTS.md` (managed include block) |
| `github` | `.github/instructions/*.instructions.md` | `.github/agents/*.agent.md` | `.github/copilot-instructions.md` (managed include block) |
| `all` | All of the above | All of the above | All of the above |

