## Pipeline Overview

A self-organizing team of agents. Each agent knows who to hand off to next based on the context it receives. Nothing ships without passing Bagnik.

```
Idea → Vadavik (spec) → Lojma (UX) + Mokash (docs, parallel)
     → Cmok /skill/ (mockups) → User UAT
     → Laznik (arch + tests) → Bagnik (test gate)
     → Cmok /agent/ (build) + Mokash (docs, parallel) → Bagnik (code QA)
     → Zlydni (commit + archive)
```

### Agents

| Agent | Беларуская | Role | Model | Mythology |
|-------|-----------|------|-------|-----------|
| Bagnik | **Багнік** | Test gate & code QA | Opus | Болотный дух — ничего не пропускает; к нему всё само приходит. |
| Cmok | **Цмок** | Build | Sonnet | Белорусский дракон — справедливый строитель сокровищ. |
| Mokash | **Мокаш** | Documentation | Sonnet | Богиня прядения — ткёт нити знаний. |
| Veles | **Вялес** | AutoResearch ratchet (self-improve) | Sonnet | Хозяин Яви/Нави/Прави — ratchet loop в трёх мирах. |
| Zlydni | **Злыдні** | Commits & version control | Haiku | Духи дома — тихо делают неизбежную работу. |

### Skills

| Skill     | Role                          |
|-----------|-------------------------------|
| Vadavik   | Spec & requirements           |
| Lojma     | UX design                     |
| Cmok      | UX mockups                    |
| Laznik    | Architecture & tests          |

### Invocation

The kit uses the **same role names** in every IDE. What changes is only the **control** your editor exposes (slash menu, `@` rules, agent picker, and so on).

**Roles**

| Kind | Names |
|------|--------|
| **Skills** | `vadavik`, `lojma`, `laznik`, `cmok` (mockups only for `cmok`) |
| **Agents** | `bagnik`, `cmok` (implementation after gates), `mokash`, `veles` (autoresearch), `zlydni` |

**Mockups vs Cmok build:** the **skill** `cmok` is mockups only. **Implementation** after Bagnik is the **agent** `cmok` in Claude/Copilot; in Cursor that agent is the subagent **`/cmok-build`** (stem from `cursor_rule_name` / `cursor_subagent_name`) so it does not clash with the **`cmok`** skill.

**How to invoke (by IDE)**

| IDE | Skills | Agents |
|-----|--------|--------|
| **Claude Code** | Slash in chat: **`/vadavik`**, **`/lojma`**, **`/laznik`**, **`/cmok`** | **`@bagnik`**, **`@cmok`**, **`@mokash`**, **`@zlydni`**, or the Agent / subagent flow with those names |
| **Cursor** | In **Agent** chat, type **`/`** and pick the skill by name (discovered automatically; see [Agent Skills](https://cursor.com/docs/context/skills)). Optional: type **`/vadavik`**-style if your build resolves it the same way. | [Custom subagents](https://cursor.com/docs/context/subagents): **`/bagnik`**, **`/cmok-build`**, **`/mokash`**, **`/zlydni`**, or ask Agent to delegate. Handoff protocol: root **`AGENTS.md`** (which includes this pipeline). |
| **GitHub Copilot** (VS Code) | No Claude-style slash; workspace instructions apply broadly—refer to **Vadavik / Lojma / Laznik / Cmok** by name in the prompt. | Open the **agents** control in Copilot Chat and choose the workspace agent (**bagnik**, **cmok**, **mokash**, **zlydni**); labels match each agent file's `name:` field (see [Custom agents in VS Code](https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/copilot/customization/custom-chat-modes)). If your build offers **`@`** participants for those agents, you can use the same names there. |

The **Handoff Map** below uses **`/…`** and **`@…`** as **short labels** for those same roles (Claude-style). Translate using the table above.

